President Obama issued a statement congratulating India on its national elections, describing it as a historic event. He praised the successful completion of the largest exercise of popular voting in the world, which has strengthened India's democracy and upheld the values of freedom and pluralism. While awaiting the formation of a new government based on the election results, President Obama acknowledged the significance of the election for the people of India, who are seen as the strength and foundation for the country's prosperity and democracy. He expressed his desire to continue working with the Indian government to enhance the partnership between the United States and India.